cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with compressing Bengali text messages using various techniques such as character masking, dictionary matching, and hyphenation algorithm. These techniques are related to natural language processing and hence, this paper could belong to the cs.CL sub-category.
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper aims to compress short messages up to an optimal level which needs minimum space and consumes less time. This objective is related to information retrieval and hence, this paper could belong to the cs.IR sub-category.
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper uses various algorithms such as associative rule of data mining and hyphenation algorithm for syllable-based compression. These algorithms are related to data structures and algorithms and hence, this paper could belong to the cs.DS sub-category.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a statistical model to choose the diagrams for compression. This technique is related to machine learning and hence, this paper could belong to the cs.LG sub-category.
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although the paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography and security, data compression is often used in secure communication protocols to reduce the amount of data transmitted. Hence, this paper could also belong to the cs.CR sub-category.
